 President Uhuru Kenyatta was yesterday briefed on preparations for the forthcoming World Under-20 Athletics Championships to be held in Nairobi between July 7 and 12 this year. The President assured the Steering Committee, led by Sports Cabinet Secretary Amina Mohammed, of his full backing and directed that all arrangements be finalised by June 1. Others who attended the meeting were Deputy President Dr William Ruto, Sports Principal Secretary Joe Okudo, Organising Committee chairman, Lt Gen (Rtd) Jackson Tuwei, CEO Myke Rabah and marketing director Zaheeda Suleman.